full_text: @RonStewart_ #nflverse for NFL, could calculate from PFF for college

Divisional round pillboxes!! KC offense. Slow day at the office for Pacheco. Watson with his customary #2 WR snaps and 1 catch, for #reasons. 8 touches for Toney, which is more than the rest of the WR group put together. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/t6DHDxrbAv

Defense. Watson has definitely taken back that #3 CB role from Williams. Cook got run at the end of the half and end of game. Chenal got a handful of snaps. Harris got half a drive from Gay. Dunlap didn't get many snaps at all. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/0oQ3w6XkMw

Here's the Jaguars numbers. All pass plays the last three drives. Jamal Agnew barely played until the drive where he fumbled, where he was in on all but the first play. LB C.Muma is maybe their version of our Harris? He got one drive, and that's it. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/CWlNmfnde9
